					<description><![CDATA[<p>Linea is a Layer 2 network built by ConsenSys to make Ethereum faster and cheaper through zk-rollups. It lets users enjoy low fees while keeping Ethereum’s security. The Linea airdrop</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/linea-airdrop/" data-wpel-link="internal">What Is Linea? Complete Guide to the Airdrop and Claim Process</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Linea is a Layer 2 network built by ConsenSys to make Ethereum faster and cheaper through zk-rollups. It lets users enjoy low fees while keeping Ethereum’s security. The Linea airdrop rewards early users who supported the network before the snapshot date. This guide explains what Linea is, how its token works, the roadmap, and how to claim your airdrop before December 9, 2025.</span></p>
<h2><b>What Is Linea?</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Layer 2 network called </span><a href="https://linea.build/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Linea</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> was created to help Ethereum grow. It uses zk-rollups, a method that executes transactions off-chain before supplying proof to Ethereum. This strategy maintains the network&#8217;s speed, affordability, and security. Customers can make cheaper transactions without having to wait for long confirmation times.</span></p>
<p>Linea&#8217;s EVM-equivalence provides significant advantages for developers. It allows for the deployment of Ethereum smart contracts with minimal to no modifications, which creates a seamless migration path. This direct compatibility saves valuable time and reduces development costs.</p>
<p><a href="https://consensys.io/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consensys</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the firm behind Infura and MetaMask, developed Linea. Since millions of people have already used these technologies, Linea has robust infrastructure support. MetaMask’s default support for Linea makes it simple for users to connect and interact with the network.</span></p>
<h3><b>How Linea Works</b></h3>
<p>Linea scales Ethereum using zk-rollups to batch multiple transactions off-chain. It then submits a single summary to Ethereum, secured by a Zero-Knowledge Proof (ZKP). This proof verifies the validity of every transaction within the bundle, all while preserving privacy.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-187689 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/howlineawork-1.png" alt="Linea Blockchain" width="1172" height="588" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The network relies on zk-SNARKs (zero-knowledge Succinct Non-interactive Argument of Knowledge). zk-SNARKs make proofs small, quick to verify, and require no back-and-forth communication. This keeps verification efficient, even for large batches of transactions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Because zk-SNARKs are compact and fast, Linea can process more transactions at lower cost while maintaining Ethereum-level security. This approach allows near-instant withdrawals, unlike optimistic rollups which often require a seven-day delay.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For developers, zk-rollups simplify building dApps by removing the need for complex dispute systems. This creates a smoother experience for DeFi protocols, NFT platforms, and games that need fast, final confirmations.</span></p>
<h3><b>Linea Team and Founder</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Linea is led by experienced people in blockchain and AI. </span><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/joseph-lubin-48406489/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Joseph Lubin</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, co-founder of Ethereum, is the Linea founder. The team also includes </span><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/redawson/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rob Dawson</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (CTO) and </span><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chris-mckibbin-68352/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chris McKibbin</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (COO). Their expertise ensures that Linea grows in the right direction and stays aligned with Ethereum’s mission.</span></p>
<h3><b>Linea Token Overview</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The network uses the LINEA token, built on </span><a href="https://ethereum.org/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ethereum</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The total supply is 72,009,990,000 LINEA. Unlike most projects, there is no token allocation for insiders or investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The token model focuses on users and ecosystem growth:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">ETH is used as the gas token, so users don’t need to hold LINEA to pay fees.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">LINEA has no governance rights and no allocations to the team or VCs.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">85% of tokens are allocated to the community &#8211; 10% through an unlocked airdrop, 75% for a 10-year ecosystem fund.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This approach rewards early supporters and encourages long-term adoption.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-187690 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Linea-Token-Allocation.png" alt="Linea Token Allocation" width="1378" height="775" /></p>
<h3><b>Linea Funding and Governance</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Microsoft, Coinbase Ventures, SoftBank, Temasek, and Animoca Brands are among the leading investors who have contributed over $725 million to ConsenSys, the company that supports Linea. This solid support ensures steadiness in finances.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-187691 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Funding-and-Governance.png" alt="Linea Funding and Governance" width="1292" height="727" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The non-profit Linea Association in Switzerland is in charge of governance. It is in charge of treasury, decentralization, and protocol development. Ethereum-native companies like Status, Eigen Labs, and ENS are partners.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Protocol transaction fees and ETH staking yield are the sources of income. Since a portion of the fees are burned, the token concept is deflationary and consistent with Ethereum&#8217;s business strategy.</span></p>
<h2><b>Linea Roadmap </b></h2>
<p><a href="https://docs.linea.build/technology/decentralization" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Linea&#8217;s development roadmap</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is divided into 5 phases that the team plans to implement sequentially with the collaboration of the Linea community and ecosystem.</span></p>
<h3><b>Phase 0 – Complete</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Phase 0 started with the launch of Linea Mainnet Alpha. The network introduced its zkEVM, making it possible for developers to migrate dApps from Ethereum without changing smart contracts.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Linea Security Council established to oversee network safety and manage risks using a multi-signature security contract. Client software for running a local node was released to the public, giving users more power to verify transactions independently and reduce reliance on the operator.</span></p>
<h3><b>Phase 1 – In Progress</b></h3>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Open Source Stack:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Linea is licensing its software under AGPL-3.0, allowing anyone to view, fork, or modify the code. This improves transparency and keeps the platform open.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>100% EVM Coverage:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Linea is working to support all EVM opcodes and precompiles. This will allow trustless execution for every use case. The arithmetic specifications will be published, audited, and included in bug bounty programs to improve reliability.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>Phase 2 – Next</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The second phase will focus on governance improvements and censorship resistance:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Diversifying the Security Council: Adding more participants will prevent power concentration and improve decision-making.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Censorship-Free Withdrawals: The network will be upgraded so that no aggregator can block withdrawals, giving users full control over their assets.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>Phase 3 – Next</b></h3>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Decentralizing Miners and Validators: To increase security and balance, the network will divide key positions, such as validators, among several participants. Although it can be technically difficult, doing this is essential to lowering trust and preventing manipulation.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Decentralized Governance: The network will expose governance to the community to ensure openness and fairness. This will limit unilateral decisions and boost network resiliency.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><b>Phase 4 – Final</b></h3>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Multi-Vendor Deployment: The system will deploy multiple zkEVM proof sources to ensure continuity, even if one fails..</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Limited Governance: The system will apply upgrades only when necessary, in response to modifications to the EVM specification, and governance will be applied only where needed.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The role of the Security Council is to maintain a balance between decentralization and government by only taking action in situations involving systemic risk or inconsistency.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><b>How To Get Linea Airdrop?</b></h2>
<p>Qualified users can claim tokens by doing the following:</p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Open the </span><a href="https://linea.build/hub" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Linea Hub</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> airdrop page.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Connect your wallet. For multisig wallets, claim via LineaScan with WalletConnect.<img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-187693" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Linea-Hub-Page.png" alt="Linea Hub Page" width="512" height="252" /><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-187695" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Log-in.png" alt="" width="512" height="309" /><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-187696" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Linea-AirDrop-Connect-Wallet-1-1.png" alt="" width="512" height="252" /></span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check your eligibility and view your token amount.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-187697 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Linea-Token-Transaction.png" alt="Linea Token Transaction" width="512" height="294" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">         4.Click the claim button after September 10, approve the transaction, and pay a small ETH fee.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Following confirmation, the LINEA tokens will show up in your wallet.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To stay safe from phishing scams, users should always visit the official website. Tokens will be returned to the ecosystem fund if they are not claimed by December 9, 2025.</span></p>
<h2><b>How To Withdraw Linea Airdrop?</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Step-by-Step Guide</span></p>
<ol>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Open the official claim contract: </span><a href="https://lineascan.build/address/0x87baa1694381ae3ecae2660d97fe60404080eb64" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://lineascan.build/address/0x87baa1694381ae3ecae2660d97fe60404080eb64</span></a></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Go to the Contract tab and select Write Contract.<img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-187698 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Airdrop-Withdrawlal.png" alt="Airdrop Withdrawlal" width="512" height="276" /></span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Connect your wallet (MetaMask or any supported option).<img decoding="async" class="wp-image-187699 size-full aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Connect-wallet-2.png" alt="" width="512" height="176" /></span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Find the Claim function and click Write:<img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-187700 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Claim-Function.png" alt="Claim Function" width="512" height="170" /><br />
</span>&#8211; If you have already claimed from the connected account, you cannot claim again, and the transaction will fail.<br />
&#8211; If the claiming period is over, the transaction will fail. The deadline is 23:59:59 UTC on December 9, 2025.<br />
&#8211; If the wallet has no tokens available, the transaction will fail.</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Approve the transaction in your wallet popup.<img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-187701" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Approve-the-Linea-transaction.png" alt="" width="512" height="273" /></span></li>
<li>After you confirm, the system will add your $LINEA tokens to your wallet.</li>
</ol>
<h2><b>What Is the Date of Linea TGE?</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The checker went live on September 3, 2025, marking the beginning of Linea&#8217;s Token Generation Event (TGE), which allowed users to confirm their eligibility prior to the claim period.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">On September 10, 2025, the formal claim window opened, and it will stay open until December 9, 2025, at 23:59 UTC. There is a ninety-day claim period. The countdown doesn&#8217;t start when you link your wallet; it starts when the claim procedure goes live.</span></p>
<p>The Linea Consortium Ecosystem Fund will return any leftover tokens after the deadline to fund the growth of the Ethereum and Linea ecosystems.</p>
<h2><b>Linea Airdrop: Conclusion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Linea appears to be one of Ethereum&#8217;s most user-friendly Layer 2 networks. Its design prioritizes actual users and builders over insiders or venture capitalists. The Linea airdrop rewards early backers and encourages them to continue expanding the ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">ConsenSys and reliable Ethereum partners support the network, lending it legitimacy and resources for sustained expansion. Even for those who are unfamiliar with Layer 2 networks, its integration with MetaMask and Infura makes it simple to utilize.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Advantages:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transparent and fair token distribution</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Strong support from ConsenSys and Ethereum-native partners</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Simple onboarding through MetaMask</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Low fees and fast transaction speed</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Long-term ecosystem fund to support developers and users</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Disadvantages:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Still new, adoption and liquidity are growing</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">LINEA token does not have governance rights</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">You cannot recover missed airdrop claims.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Competing with other Layer 2 solutions like Arbitrum and Optimism</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Although it is still in its infancy, Linea is an intriguing project to follow because of its well-defined path, emphasis on decentralization, and dedication to the community.</span></p>
